<|asst|>
As an AI assistant, I don't have personal thoughts or opinions. However, I can tell you what experts generally agree on. 

The prices of non-fungible tokens (NFTs) can be significantly influenced by the fluctuations in cryptocurrency values since NFT purchases are usually made with cryptocurrencies like Ether. 

When cryptocurrency prices go up, investors have more buying power, and the reverse is true when cryptocurrency prices drop. Therefore, a surge in the value of cryptocurrencies can lead to an increase in the prices of NFTs and a greater number of sales. 

On the other hand, if cryptocurrency prices decrease significantly, it can cause a slowdown in the NFT market as potential buyers might be hesitant to spend their devalued currencies on NFTs.

Please note that the NFT market is complex and can be influenced by many different factors beyond cryptocurrency values, such as overarching economic trends, the perceived value of the digital assets, and market speculation. Always consider multiple factors when evaluating the NFT market.
<|end|>
