"The Queen's Gambit" is a dramatic series that premiered on Netflix in 2020. Based on the novel of the same name by Walter Tevis, the series revolves around the life of an orphan chess prodigy named Beth Harmon.

Set during the Cold War era, the story begins in the mid-1950s and proceeds into the 1960s. The series explores Beth's rise to the top of the chess world while struggling with drug and alcohol dependency, as well as emotional problems and self-doubt.

Beth is taught chess by the custodian at the orphanage where she resides. As the story unfolds, the audience learns along with Beth that there's a price to pay for her genius, and she struggles to find her place in the world.

"The Queen's Gambit" has been praised for its writing, performance, and its accurate portrayal of the game of chess, earning the series a place in the list of popular shows watched all over the world.
