<|user|>
Could you explain what "gross profit" means in simple terms?
<|end|>
<|asst|>
Sure, in simple terms, "gross profit" refers to the total revenue a company makes from selling its products or services minus the direct costs associated with producing those products or services. These direct costs can include the cost of raw materials and labor used in the creation of the product or the delivery of the service. Gross profit does not take into account other costs like overhead expenses, taxes, and other operational costs. It's one way to measure how efficiently a company uses its resources to produce and sell its goods or services.
<|end|>
<|user|>
Alright, can you tell me about the gross profit of Amazon, Inc?
<|end|>
<|asst|>
