2. Main Course: A variety of keto dishes to fill your lunch or dinner plate.
3. Desserts: Keto doesn't mean you can't enjoy sweets. Try some keto-friendly desserts!
4. Snacks: Stay satiated between meals with these keto-friendly snacks.
5. Beverages: Complement your meals with a refreshing keto-friendly drink.
6. Side Dishes: Boost your main meal with these delightful keto sides.

These categories can guide you in starting your ketogenic diet by giving you an array of dishes to choose from. Enjoy your journey into keto cooking!
<|end|>
<|user|>
Starting a new diet sounds a bit difficult. Do you have any tips for staying motivated?
<|end|>
<|asst|>
Keeping up with a new diet can indeed be challenging, especially in the beginning. Here are some tips to help you stay motivated:

1. Set clear, attainable goals: Visualizing your goals can help drive your determination to stick to your new diet.

2. Start small: Don't try to make drastic changes all at once. Gradually incorporate the diet into your lifestyle.

3. Plan your meals ahead: This will help you stay on track and avoid last-minute unhealthy food choices.

4. Find recipes you genuinely enjoy: The keto diet can be very diverse and delicious. Experiment with different recipes to keep your meals interesting.

5. Be patient with yourself: Understand that progress takes time and it's okay to have setbacks.

6. Celebrate small victories: Every step you take towards your goal is an achievement. 

Remember, changing your dietary habits is a personal journey. It's about feeling good and healthy rather than being perfect. Keep a positive mindset, and take it one meal at a time!
<|end|>
