I have a new record from our sales database that I need to convert into a Java object, validate it against our SalesData class, and then generate a mapping for a database table update. The record is '{"id":"1234", "name":"John Doe", "sale_date":"2022-09-21", "amount":500}', and the table name is 'sales'. The validation rules are [{"fieldName":"id", "validationPattern":"^\\d+$"}, {"fieldName":"name", "validationPattern":"^[\\w\\s]+$"}, {"fieldName":"sale_date", "validationPattern":"^\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}$"}, {"fieldName":"amount", "validationPattern":"^\\d+$"}].
