<|end|>
<|tool|>
[{"name": "agriculture.get_crop_yield", "results": {"crop_yield": [{"date": "2026-03-01", "yield": 120, "weather_conditions": "Sunny"}, {"date": "2026-03-02", "yield": 115, "weather_conditions": "Partly Cloudy"}, {"date": "2026-03-03", "yield": 118, "weather_conditions": "Cloudy"}, {"date": "2026-03-04", "yield": 115, "weather_conditions": "Rain"}, {"date": "2026-03-05", "yield": 117, "weather_conditions": "Heavy Rain"}, {"date": "2026-03-06", "yield": 121, "weather_conditions": "Sunny"}, {"date": "2026-03-07", "yield": 123, "weather_conditions": "Sunny"}]}}]
<|end|>
<|asst|>
[agriculture.get_weather_impact(location="Fresno", time_period={"start_date": "2026-03-01", "end_date": "2026-03-07"}, crop_type="Wheat")]
<|end|>
<|tool|>
[{"name": "agriculture.get_weather_impact", "results": {"weather_impact": [{"date": "2026-03-01", "impact_level": "None", "weather_conditions": "Sunny"}, {"date": "2026-03-02", "impact_level": "Low", "weather_conditions": "Partly Cloudy"}, {"date": "2026-03-03", "impact_level": "Low", "weather_conditions": "Cloudy"}, {"date": "2026-03-04", "impact_level": "Medium", "weather_conditions": "Rain"}, {"date": "2026-03-05", "impact_level": "High", "weather_conditions": "Heavy Rain"}, {"date": "2026-03-06", "impact_level": "None", "weather_conditions": "Sunny"}, {"date": "2026-03-07", "impact_level": "None", "weather_conditions": "Sunny"}]}}]
<|end|>
<|asst|>
The estimated crop yield for wheat in Fresno from March 1st to March 7th ranges from 115 to 123 units per day, with different weather conditions affecting the yield. Regarding the expected impact of weather conditions, there are no significant concerns for March 1st and 6th to 7th, low impact on 2nd to 3rd, a medium impact on the 4th, and high impact due to heavy rain on the 5th. It would be advisable to take protective measures for the crops, especially on the days with moderate to high impact.
<|end|>


